Printability

Literature review

  • Last update: 2019-12-17
  • Work document for Anezka research.

Goal: The main goal of this document is to make a systematic literature review about the notion Printability from a rheology perspective

Specific goals:

  • Definition of printability from literature.
  • Map the rheology measurements used in 3D printing. Establish what correlations of rheology to printing process.
  • Identify requirements to consider for an open source hardware.

Methodology

Methodology for the search of literature

Research question

Review protocol

  1. Type of doucments: Only journals
  2. Keywords:
    • fused deposition modelling, fused filament fabrication, 3D printing
    • rheology, viscosity
    • polymer
  3. Search strategy
    • (fused deposition modeling OR 3D printing OR fused filament fabrication) AND (rheology OR viscosity) AND polymer)

  4. Datbases: Web of Science

  5. Study selection criteria
    • Papers related to engineering
  6. Study selection procedure
    • First filter: Read Title and Abstract
    • Second : Read intro and conclusions
